Five people died when a truck collided head-on with a car in Mochadi village, near St Ritas hospital outside Groblersdal. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the accident happened on Wednesday afternoon. One passenger from the car survived with serious injuries and five other occupants including the driver, died instantly. The deceased are three adults and two toddlers. Ngoepe said the eight passengers who were being transported in a truck including the driver, sustained serious injuries and were taken to hospital for medical treatment. He said the process of identifying the deceased is still underway. Ngoepe added that the cause of the accident is not clear at this stage, but ongoing police investigations will tell.